However, CalCentral is known to have technical problems and staff offices close at 4pm or 5pm. I wouldn't suggest waiting until midnight.

Regarding your waitlist question: no you don't get dropped right away, but rather the enrollment managers try to get you in the class if there is space. If that fails, only then you're dropped. Therefore, you should choose to stay in the waitlist only if you seriously want to be in the class because there is no going back!
